  "prompt": "How do I focus?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help improve focus:\n\n1. Minimize distractions\n- Turn off phone notifications\n- Use website blockers\n- Create a quiet workspace\n\n2. Time management techniques\n- Pomodoro Technique (25 min work, 5 min break)\n- Time blocking\n- Set specific goals\n\n3. Physical and mental preparation\n- Get enough sleep\n- Exercise regularly\n- Practice meditation or mindfulness\n- Eat a balanced diet\n\n4. Improve your environment\n- Organize your workspace\n- Use good lighting\n- Maintain comfortable temperature\n- Use noise-canceling headphones\n\n5. Mental strategies\n- Break large tasks into smaller steps\n- Start with the most challenging task\n- Use to-do lists\n- Practice single-tasking\n\n6. Reduce mental clutter\n- Practice stress management\n- Take regular breaks\n- Stay hydrated\n- Limit caffeine intake\n\n7. Consider potential underlying issues\n- Check for ADHD\n- Address potential mental health concerns\n- Consult a professional if focus problems persist\n\n8. Use productivity tools\n- Digital planners\n- Focus apps\n- Time tracking software\n\nRemember, improving focus is a skill that takes practice and patience.",
